 <!-- FAQs Widget ******************* -->

<FAQs
title="Frequently Asked Questions"
subtitle="Dive into the following questions to gain insights into the Inflation Reduction Act and how it impacts your energy choices."
classes={{ container: 'max-w-6xl' }}
items={[
  {
    title: 'What types of equipment are eligible for the Efficient Home Improvement Credit in 2025?',
    description:
      "Eligible equipment must meet the highest efficiency tier set by the Consortium for Energy Efficiency (CEE). For alternative oil furnaces, they must meet 2021 Energy Star efficiency criteria and be rated for specific fuel blends.",
  },
  {
    title: 'What are the requirements for the Residential Clean Energy Property Credit?',
    description:
      "Solar water heating systems must be certified by the Solar Rating Certification Corporation or a comparable entity. Geothermal heat pumps must meet Energy Star program requirements, and battery storage must have a capacity of 3 kilowatt-hours or greater.",
  },
  {
    title: 'Can I claim credits for improvements made to my second home or rental property?',
    description:
      "Yes, credits are available for certain improvements made to second homes. Renters may also be eligible if they make eligible improvements to their principal residence.",
  },
  {
    title: 'When can I claim these credits?',
    description:
      "Credits can only be claimed in the year the property is installed. There is no lifetime limit, but yearly limits do apply.",
  },
  {
    title: 'Can these credits be carried forward to the next tax year?',
    description:
      "The ability to carry forward credits varies by credit type. Please consult the specific guidelines for each credit to determine eligibility.",
  },
  {
    title: 'How do subsidies and rebates affect the amount of credit I can claim?',
    description:
      "Subsidies and rebates may affect the amount of credit that can be claimed. Both credits are nonrefundable and can offset the Alternative Minimum Tax (AMT).",
  },
]}
/>

  
